239
00:17:20,639 --> 00:17:24,676
<i>The members' expressions
and moves are captured more dynamically.</i>

240
00:17:30,315 --> 00:17:31,350
Cut!

241
00:17:32,217 --> 00:17:35,888
{\an8}-Isn't fatigue building?
-Well, lactic acid sure builds up.

242
00:17:35,954 --> 00:17:38,123
-We're going on next.
-Yes.

243
00:17:38,190 --> 00:17:39,158
See you.

244
00:17:39,224 --> 00:17:42,861
<i>And this is the video that was filmed...</i>

245
00:17:44,696 --> 00:17:51,470
"KYUKENSHI"

246
00:18:15,461 --> 00:18:18,263
<i>And this jump...</i>

247
00:18:22,901 --> 00:18:24,503
{\an8}<i>Ten days before filming,</i>

248
00:18:24,570 --> 00:18:27,639
{\an8}<i>Sakuma was here rehearsing.</i>

249
00:18:29,975 --> 00:18:33,312
DECEMBER 2018

250
00:18:34,179 --> 00:18:35,247
This is amazing!

251
00:18:36,115 --> 00:18:38,951
<i>Acrobatic moves
are his ultimate specialty.</i>

252
00:18:39,852 --> 00:18:42,054
Try to feel how it goes once.

253
00:18:42,121 --> 00:18:47,025
<i>For Sakuma, there was a contraption
he had to master this time.</i>

254
00:18:48,627 --> 00:18:50,629
-Whoa!
-Like that just now.

255
00:18:50,696 --> 00:18:53,332
Try not to kick it yourself.

256
00:18:53,398 --> 00:18:57,903
If you try to kick it, the timing
will be off and you'll miss the lift.

257
00:19:00,205 --> 00:19:04,309
<i>If the timing isn't correct,
it could lead to serious injuries.</i>

258
00:19:05,978 --> 00:19:07,679
-I'll try it.
-Okay.

259
00:19:08,714 --> 00:19:09,815
All right!

260
00:19:12,784 --> 00:19:14,153
-Here I go!
-Okay.

261
00:19:18,357 --> 00:19:19,858
You'll hurt your knees...

262
00:19:19,925 --> 00:19:21,927
It completely got me.

263
00:19:24,396 --> 00:19:25,631
You mean like this?

264
00:19:25,697 --> 00:19:26,832
Yeah, like that.

265
00:19:31,303 --> 00:19:32,271
Here I go.

266
00:19:34,806 --> 00:19:35,741
I see!

267
00:19:36,241 --> 00:19:39,411
Ugh, I don't understand! What is this?

268
00:19:39,978 --> 00:19:40,812
Here I go.

269
00:19:47,286 --> 00:19:51,823
Hm, I still don't understand.
I can't grasp it at all.

270
00:19:51,890 --> 00:19:54,960
-Try it a few times to get the feel of it.
-True.

271
00:19:56,762 --> 00:19:59,264
<i>As Miyadate watches over...</i>

272
00:20:02,134 --> 00:20:03,468
Okay!

273
00:20:03,535 --> 00:20:06,171
<i>He succeeds on his thirteenth try.</i>

274
00:20:06,238 --> 00:20:07,973
That one was great!

275
00:20:08,040 --> 00:20:09,541
That one was nice!

276
00:20:10,509 --> 00:20:11,543
Yes.

277
00:20:11,610 --> 00:20:12,878
<i>One more time.</i>

278
00:20:13,946 --> 00:20:15,547
-Please, go ahead.
-Here I go.

279
00:20:19,151 --> 00:20:21,153
-Yeah!
-Nice!

280
00:20:21,220 --> 00:20:22,454
Yay.

281
00:20:22,521 --> 00:20:24,223
Is it easier if we lift it?

282
00:20:24,289 --> 00:20:25,257
I think so.

283
00:20:25,324 --> 00:20:27,659
It depends on how it feels for you.

284
00:20:28,193 --> 00:20:32,698
Like, whatever you do in acrobatics
is always scary at first, you know.

285
00:20:32,764 --> 00:20:37,703
And as you get used to doing it,
your fear starts to fade.

286
00:20:37,769 --> 00:20:41,940
To overcome your fear
is probably most important.

287
00:20:42,474 --> 00:20:48,080
Well, in my case, I happen
to be able to dance and do acrobatics,

288
00:20:48,146 --> 00:20:49,881
but I really suck at sports.

289
00:20:49,948 --> 00:20:53,585
I'm a slow runner.
I can't swim freestyle either.

290
00:20:54,086 --> 00:20:56,288
Tomorrow, I'll be walking like this.

291
00:21:00,459 --> 00:21:05,564
<i>Each one of the members has
been polishing their own unique skills.</i>

292
00:21:11,303 --> 00:21:15,173
<i>At last, the day to film
that one performance has come.</i>

293
00:21:15,240 --> 00:21:16,375
